bib_record.title: 0+ states in deformed actinide nuclei by the (p,t) reaction

free_txt: New analysis for 232Th(p,t)230Th was given. A lot of
new data for partial angular distributions were added.
The reaction products have been analyzed
with the Q3D magnetic spectrograph and detected in its
focal plane. Two different focal plane detectors which
are multiwire proportional chambers with readout of a
cathode foil structure for position determination and
dE/Erest particle identification
Relative errors from counting statistics
and background subtraction
Tables received from Dr. H.-F.Wirth and
Dr. A.I.Levon (for 232Th(p,t)230Th reaction)
Entry approved by Dr. H.-F.Wirth
The target 230Th had a thickness of 100 mg/cm2,
evaporated onto 22 mg/cm2 thick carbon backings.
The isotopic purity of the 230Th target was about 99%.
The target 232Th had a thickness of 100 mg/cm2,
evaporated onto 22 mg/cm2 thick carbon backings.
The targets 234U had a thickness of 100 mg/cm2 each,
evaporated onto 22 mg/cm2 thick carbon backings.
The isotopic purity of the 234U target was about 99%.
